      "writtenOn": "2020-12-23T22:02:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Zeroing out half a KB every time we stroke a path seems like a lot of overhead. Something like chalkboard wouldn\u0027t be as affected because each path has a lot of verbs. The torture case would be drawing a ton of paths where each one has a single verb. That being said, I tried to create a torture case like this to benchmark locally and it didn\u0027t seem that bad.\n\nThis solution should be fine, although I still don\u0027t love doing extra work just to silence our own internal valgrind runs. An alternative would be to just disable \"USE_SIMD\" when RUNNING_ON_VALGRIND is true.. Thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "2d24a906_049deb8b",
      "range": {
